	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your<lb/> letters of the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Ins came<lb/> duly to hand&#44; since which<lb/> a box containing<lb/> 2 of the New Edition<lb/> of the 40 Bible with the<lb/> parcels pr <persName>Cohen</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Jacobs</persName>&#44; <persName>Mois</persName> &#38; <persName>Bradl<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> have been safely landed<lb/> &#38; all the parcels deli<lb/>vered &#38; forwarded as<lb/> directed.</p>
				<p>You ask for the docu<lb/>ments in relation to the<lb/> debate that took place<lb/> between <persName>Dr Raphall</persName><lb/> <persName>PB</persName> &#38; <persName>Wise</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr. Levin</persName><lb/> took down the debate<lb/> at the occasion &#38; trans<lb/>mitted them to <persName>Dr. R</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>&#38; which no doubt the<lb/> Dr. has still in his pos<lb/>session &#38; which you no<lb/> doubt can obtain upon<lb/> application to him &#44; besides<lb/> this further evidence can<lb/> be obtained at <placeName>Albany</placeName><lb/> from the Synagogue&#44; or<lb/> the party who opposed<lb/> <persName>Wise</persName> return to them after<lb/> he had accepted the<lb/> situation of the ministry<lb/> of the <placeName>Haul St </placeName>Synagogue<lb/>  My affadavit are amongst<lb/> its records in addition<lb/> to others &#38; the whole pro<lb/>ceedings as it occurred here<lb/> in that memorable<lb/> debate &#38; examination<lb/> but really the Bird is</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>not worth the powder<lb/> &#38; I trust &#38; hope that<lb/> you will treat the<lb/> Wise man of the Well<lb/> with contempt &#38; not<lb/> notice him or his dia<lb/>bolical remarks.  I agree<lb/> with <persName>Dr. R</persName> that it can<lb/> not add to your fame<lb/> &#38; is rather derogatory to<lb/> your clerical dignity<lb/> to be continually excited<lb/> into a polemic with<lb/> a man of such mean<lb/> &#38; contemptible shifts &#38;<lb/> <sic>&#38;</sic> perversity.  Ere this<lb/> is to hand you have been<lb/> advised of <persName>Revd Mayer</persName><lb/> resignation of his charge<lb/> of the <placeName>Haul St.</placeName> Synagogue<lb/> to take place after the</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>coming day of atone<lb/>ment&#44; It has long<lb/> been a matter of<lb/> <sic>surprize</sic> to us that<lb/> he has not long since<lb/> done what he has now<lb/> accomplished&#44; for really<lb/> the contempt &#38; indiffer<lb/>ence with which he<lb/> has been treated has<lb/> been such that no<lb/> Revd who had the least<lb/> respect for himself &#38;<lb/> his calling ought to have<lb/> submitted to such indig<lb/>nity.  The congregation<lb/> is dead &#38; reform after<lb/> 20 years efforts has gone<lb/> as it was predicted.<lb/>  What will be the next move<lb/> of the Reformers time only will<lb/> dissolve.  Your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen.</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Sept 9 1859</date></p>
		</body>
